mmissioned officers in the United States Air Force  Captain Warren commissioned in the Air Force on 9 May 2009 through the AFROTC program at Oklahoma State University as an Intelligence Officer  He attended Intelligence Training School at Goodfellow AFB  San Angelo Texas  Upon graduation  Capt Warren was assigned to the 3rd Operational Support Squadron  Elmendorf AFB  Anchorage  Alaska where he was tasked with supporting the 3rd Wing s assets  C 17s  C 130s  F 22s  E 3s and HH 60  While at Elmendorf AFB  Capt Warren was selected to be the Intelligence Chief of the 517 Airlift Squadron where  in addition to supporting the C 17 s worldwide missions  he supported numerous exercises including RED FLAG Alaska  Operation Tomodachi in Japan  Ulchi Freedom Guardian in Korea and Cope Tiger in Thailand  As his next assignment  Captain Warren was selected to serve at the AFROTC Detachment 880  Virginia Military Institute  Lexington  VA  where he is currently assigned  EDUCATION 2006 Bachelor of Science degree in Business Management  Oklahoma State University  OK 2009 Air and Space Basic Training  Maxwell AFB  AL ASSIGNMENTS 1  June 2009   May 2010  Student  Intelligence Training School  Goodfellow AFB  TX 2  May 2010   Nov 2013  517 AS Chief of Intelligence  3rd Operational Support Squadron  Elmendorf AFB  AK 3  Nov 2013   Present  Operations Flight Commander  AFROTC Detachment 880  Virginia Military Institute  Lexington  VA MAJOR AWARDS AND DECORATIONS Air Force Commendation Medal National Defense Service Medal Global War on Terrorism Service Medal Humanitarian Service Medal PROFESSIONAL MEMBERSHIPS AND AFFILIATIONS Air Force Association Military Officers Association of America EFFECTIVE DATES OF PROMOTION  Second Lieutenant May 27  2009 First Lieutenant May 27  2011 Captain May 27  2013  Current as of February 2015  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimin